sentences: John Boswell (born 1945) is a book packager, literary agent, and author in New York City.
Two books he co-wrote, French for Cats (1992, with Henry Beard) and O.J.'s Legal Pad (1995, with Henry Beard and Ron Barrett), have reached the New York Times Best Seller list.
